<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09152f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09152f">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09152f"> 152(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">A</font> calls child father ~ <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n09152f"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Fancy a <mark>mother so anxious to say &ldquo;please&rdquo; to her child that she calls him &ldquo;Father&rdquo;</mark> as an equivalent for &ldquo;please,&rdquo; then puts it all in the subjunctive mood to soften off her maternal request for some small service he renders her. <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 108</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
